race.description: Mon Natural Foods Mark Goring Memorial Handicap
race.comment: TORVECCHIO (11) ran a solid race first up at Hamilton over 1200m in a similar race, drawing wide and working home well to be beaten 2.5 lengths. She'll be much better suited getting up in trip now and can finish over the top of them. JINGU EXPRESS (6) is coming off a tough win at Wangaratta when well backed as an even money favourite and can go on with it despite rising slightly in grade. MISS LOTTIE (7) struggles to win but hasn't been far away in two runs back and should be peaking now. She can roll forward from that gate and if she can slot in she'll take some beating. TOP HONOURS (3) resumes. His fresh run at Seymour last time in was quite good for this, he can surprise. OLNEY (1) has a tough draw but is the class of the field and can win this fresh.
